### Pipeline Protection
* Infrastructure Security: 
Filter traffic to prohibit unauthorised ingress/egress
Runners

* SLSA Framework: (Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts)

Level 1 – Provenance
Scripted build
Build metadata generated

Level 2 – Signed Provenance
Provenance digitally signed
Tamper-evident

Level 3 – Hardened Builds
Isolated, hermetic builds
Strong CI/CD security

Level 4 – Highest Assurance
Maximum security
For regulated/high-security environments

* STRIDE 

* Secret Management & Hiding
Detection: Use pre-commit hooks to detect secrets before code is committed.
OIDC: Use OpenID Connect for cloud authentication instead of storing long-lived access keys.
Rotation: Automatically rotate secrets/credentials regularly to reduce compromise risk.
